# Privacy Policy — ShiftSync (WFM Schedule to Calendar)

**Last updated: July 16, 2026**

ShiftSync ("the extension") is a browser extension that copies the work schedule
shown on your NICE WFM (WebStation) pages into your own Google Calendar. This
policy explains exactly what the extension does and does not do with your
information.

## The short version

- ShiftSync runs entirely **in your browser**.
- It does **not** send your schedule or any personal data to the developer or to
  any third-party server.
- The only place your schedule data is sent is **your own Google Calendar**, and
  only when you sync.
- ShiftSync does **not** collect analytics, does **not** track you, does **not**
  show ads, and does **not** sell or share data with anyone.

## What information ShiftSync accesses

When you view your schedule in NICE WebStation and run a sync (manually or via
auto-sync), the extension reads the schedule content already displayed on that
page. This can include:

- Shift, break, meeting, and activity times and labels
- The date range shown
- Your name, as displayed on the schedule page (used to name and select the
  correct calendar)

It also stores a small set of **preferences** you set in the popup:

- Whether auto-sync on page load is enabled
- Your "My Calendar Name" override, if you enter one
- A one-time flag recording that you confirmed the first automatic import (and
  any ±1-hour time adjustment you selected)

## How that information is used

- The schedule content is converted, **locally in your browser**, into a standard
  calendar file (ICS).
- That file is imported into your Google Calendar using Google Calendar's own
  import screen, which the extension opens on your behalf.
- Your preferences are saved locally using the browser's extension storage so the
  extension remembers your settings between sessions.

## Where your information goes

| Data | Where it goes | Who can see it |
|------|---------------|----------------|
| Your parsed schedule (ICS) | Your Google Calendar account | You (and whoever you share that calendar with) |
| Your preferences | Local browser storage on your device | You |
| Anything else | Nowhere — it is not transmitted | — |

ShiftSync has **no backend server**. The developer never receives, stores, or has
access to your schedule or personal data.

## Data retention

- Preferences remain in local browser storage until you change them, clear the
  extension's data, or uninstall the extension.
- Parsed schedule data is held only transiently in local storage during a sync and
  is not retained afterward beyond what your Google Calendar stores.

## Third-party services

The extension interacts with **Google Calendar** (calendar.google.com) to perform
the import. Your use of Google Calendar is governed by Google's own privacy policy.
The extension does not use any other third-party services.

## Children's privacy

ShiftSync is a workplace productivity tool intended for adults in a work setting
and is not directed at children.

